cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC

This paper deals with the problem of discriminating word senses, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses complex networks and learning techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of topological patterns, which is related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
